1 adopt and post written policies that identify
2 nonpublic areas, establish procedures for warrant
3 verification and staff response, prohibit the
4 collection of certain iininigration-status data, and
5 require annual staff training and certain multilingual
6 notices; and
7 (2) Require the attorney general to publish model
8 policies.
9 SECTION 2. (a) By January 1, 2027, all state and county
10 agencies that operate protected community locations shall adopt
11 and post written policies that:
12 (1) Identify nonpublic areas;
13 (2) Establish procedures for warrant verification and
14 staff response;
15 (3) Prohibit the collection of immigration-status data
16 unless required by law;
17 (4) Require annual staff training; and
18 (5) Require multilingual notices stating that services are
19 provided regardless of immigration status.
20 (b) The attorney general shall publish model policies for
21 adoption by all state and county agencies that operate protected
