1 community locations and voluntary adoption by private education
2 or health providers and private places of worship.
3 (c) For the purposes of this section:
4 "Nonpublic area" means any area of a facility that is not
5 open to the general public.
6 "Protected community location" means any facility operated
7 by the State or a county.
8 SECTION 3. This Act is of statewide concern, in accordance
9 with article X, section 6 of the Hawaii State Constitution.
10 Nothing in this Act restricts the university of Hawaii from
11 complying with mandatory federal contractor certifications or
12 other conditions tied to federal funding.
13 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.
